msContents.summary: A collection of three Aristotle commentaries bound together, the first and last are unsigned manuscript commentaries in the same hand, bound with a printed essay on Aristotle's Physica by a seventeenth-century Benedictine monk named Peter Feichtinger, dated 1633.

msItem.title: Commentarius et tractatus unicus in 4 libros Aristotelis de coelo
msItem.author: Feichtinger, Petrus

supportDesc.extent: 205 leaves : 197 x 151 (162 x 115) mm. bound to 207 x 160 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i (contemporary paper) + 203 + i (contemporary paper); 1-77, [iii], [p. 1-28] (printed pagination), 1-110; contemporary foliation in ink, upper outer corners; [1-203], modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by a single hand.

binding.p: Contemporary blind-tooled pigskin, brass catches and clasps intact.

origin.p: Second work by Peter Feichtinger was printed at Salisburg by Christopher Katzenberger, 1633.

history.provenance: Sold by Michael R. Thompson Rare Books (Los Angeles, Calif.), 1995.
